Durban - Police are still searching for the suspects who shot dead an 11-year-old in a cross fire in Ladysmith on Wednesday afternoon. According to KZN police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane a 28-year-old man had been walking along Ihlokoloko Street, E Section when an unknown man alighted from his vehicle and opened fire, fatally wounding the victim. Zwane said the victim sustained bullet wounds to his back and abdominal area and died on scene. "The 11-year-old boy was struck by a stray bullet and sustained gunshot wounds at the back of his right ear and on the shoulder and was certified dead at the scene." He said two counts of murder were opened at Ezakheni police station for investigation. "No arrests have been made and the motive for the attack is unknown." There are still no arrests following the shooting of a Richards Bay resident. The 58 year old panel beater is critical in hospital. He was shot 8 times. POST 